Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Quarter @dill pickle{1} lengthwise. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @red onion{1}.

Cut @Yukon Gold potatoes{12} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @vegetable oil{}, @fry seasoning{1}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack, flipping halfway through, until golden brown and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Add onion and cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and softened, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> TIP: If onion begins to brown too quickly, add a splash of water.

Stir in @balsamic vinegar{5%tbsp} and @sugar{1%tsp}. Continue cooking until caramelized and jammy, ~{2-3%minutes} more. Season with salt and pepper. Turn off heat; transfer to a #small bowl{}. Wash out pan.

Mince or grate @garlic clove{1}. In a second small bowl, combine @mayonnaise{2%tbsp}, @sour cream{2%tbsp}, @Dijon mustard{2%tsp}, and minced garlic to taste. Season with salt and pepper. Halve @brioche buns{2}; toast until golden.

Season @Beyond Burgers{8} all over with salt and pepper. Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for onion over medium-high heat. Add patties and cook until browned, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Top each patty with @Gouda cheese{2%slices}. Reduce heat to medium; cover pan until cheese is melted, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Spread bottom buns with half the @ketchup{4%tbsp} and top buns with a thin layer of aioli. Fill buns with patties and as much onion jam as you like. Serve with potato wedges, pickle spears, and remaining aioli and ketchup on the side.